{"course_name": "Business Analytics and Data Visualization Using SAS", "description": "Marketing has always used data for developing strategies to build, manage, and retain relationships with prospects and customers. However, recent technological advancements in collecting, storing, processing, and transmitting information have resulted in an increased reliance on data for strategic planning and execution.  This course prepares students to turn business data into actionable information.  The semester is organized into two modules: SAS Enterprise Guide and SAS JMP\u2014software systems for data integration/transformation, analysis and visualization.  Students will learn how to use the technology in the context of their applications to sales, marketing, and customer relationship management (CRM).  Although our focus will be the use of SAS Enterprise Guide and SAS JMP, the course will cover other methodologies.  Students will learn by doing: that is, guided by the instructor and using software and assigned readings/videos, they will prepare and analyze real-world data sets to learn how to develop strategic recommendations for managerial actions. \n\nStudents who successfully complete the course requirements should be able to:\n\n-\tManage data, including\no\tData access\no\tData cleansing\no\tData preparation\n\n-\tApply techniques for converting data to information, including\no\tData exploration\no\tSummarization\no\tVisualization\n\n-\tAnalyze data\no\tInteractive exploratory analytics\no\tIntroductory predictive analytics\n\r      ", "classification": "INTG1-GC", "grading": "GC SCPS Graded", "class_name": "", "meet_data": "[{'start': '6.10 PM', 'end': '8.40 PM', 'day': 'Mon'}]", "notes": "", "instructors": [], "component": "Laboratory", "number": "2300", "loc_code": "MT", "session": {"start": "09/08/2014", "end": "12/15/2014", "day": ""}, "college": "School of Continuing and Professional Studies", "location": "", "units": "3", "is_open": false, "section": "002"}
